<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-23T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-23T03:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/5186: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-23T11:00:00+03:00">February 23, 1937—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 24—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>54. My 44, February 18, 2 p.m. The Governor sent an officer to the
                                Legation this morning to inform it that the ordinance in question
                                would not be enforced as regards the clause to which I objected.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>